{"title_page": "New Yorkers in journalism", "text_new": "{{Multiple issues|\n{{famous|date=March 2019}}\n{{BLP sources|date=April 2020}}\n}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{short description|Wikimedia list article}}\n[[New York City]] has been called the [[Media in New York City|media]] capital of the world.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.statista.com/chart/3299/new-york-is-the-worlds-media-capital/ |title=New York Is The World's Media Capital |author=Felix Richter |publisher=Statista |date=March 11, 2015 |accessdate=September 22, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.lgbtqnation.com/2017/05/first-nyc-pridefest-will-televised/ |title=ABC will broadcast New York's pride parade live for the first time |author=Dawn Ennis |publisher=LGBTQ Nation |date=May 24, 2017 |accessdate=September 22, 2018|quote=Never before has any TV station in the entertainment and news media capital of the world carried what organizer boast is the world\u2019s largest Pride parade live on TV.}}</ref> An integral component of this status is the significant array of [[journalist]]s who report about international, American, and [[New York metropolitan area]]-related matters from [[Manhattan]].\n\n{{Compact ToC|pre1=Notable New Yorkers in journalism|prebreak=yes|seealso=yes|refs=yes|e=|i=|u=|x=}}\n\n==New Yorkers in journalism==\n{{Image frame|width=354|content=\n<gallery mode=packed heights=100 style=\"width:350px; background:#fafafa;font-size:85%; line-height:130%;\">\nFile:john_avlon_pic.jpg|[[John Avlon]]\nFile:Pulitzer2018-dean-baquet-20180530-wp.jpg|[[Dean Baquet]]\nFile:Brooke Baldwin on set in DC.jpg|[[Brooke Baldwin]]\nFile:Josh Barro.jpg|[[Josh Barro]]\nFile:Maria Bartiromo.jpg|[[Maria Bartiromo]]\nFile:Joybeharpic.jpg|[[Joy Behar]]\nFile:John Berman.jpg|[[John Berman]]\nFile:Charles blow 2014.jpg|[[Charles Blow]]\nFile:Kate Bolduan.jpg|[[Kate Bolduan]]\nFile:Keith Boykin 2017.jpg|[[Keith Boykin]]\nFile:Malan breton2.jpg|[[Malan Breton]]\nFile:Tom Brokaw 2015.JPG|[[Tom Broka