e antennas should be ceased until deactivation is confirmed. The Wavecontrol\u2019s WaveMon<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.wavecontrol.com/rfsafety/en/products/personal-safety|title=WaveMon RF personal monitors|website=Wavecontrol}}</ref> and Narda's RadMan 2[29] can be body-worn, and used off the body as a probe or as a monitor. Most of the RF monitors such as the FieldSENSE, EME Guard, WaveMon and the RadMan 2 also have a data logging functionality that can log the RF exposure of a worker over time.<ref name=\"narda-sts\">{{cite web|url=http://www.narda-sts.us/pdf_files/DataSheets/Radman_DataSheet.pdf |title=Narda Safety Test Solutions |publisher=Narda-sts.us |date= |accessdate=2012-04-02}}</ref><ref name=\"EME Guard\"/> The RadMan 2XT's RF detection mode with its tone search feature can locate leaks in waveguides and verify that an antenna is turned off. [https://www.narda-sts.com/en/personal-safety-emf/radman-2-xt-radman-2-lt-radman-radman-xt/ <nowiki>[30]</nowiki>]<br />\n\n==List of personal RF monitors==\n*  EME Guard <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rsicorp.com/products/rf-safety-products/eme-guard.php |title=EME Guard - MVG (Satimo) |publisher=RSIcorp.com |date=2016-06-06 |accessdate=2016-06-06}}</ref> \n*  EME Guard XS<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rsicorp.com/products/rf-safety-products/eme-guard-xs.php |title=EME Guard XS - RSIcorp.com MVG (Satimo) | publisher=RSIcorp.com |date=2016-06-06 |accessdate=2016-06-06}}</ref> \n* EME SPY 201<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rsicorp.com/products/rf-safety-products/eme-spy-201.php |title=EME SPY 201 - MVG (Satimo)}}</ref> \n* Narda Radman XT <ref name=\"Radman Mobile\">{{cite web|url=http://www.narda-sts.us/pdf_files/DataSheets/RadMan_DataSheet.pdf|title=Narda Radman XT|last=|first=|date=2011-06-06|website=|publisher=Narda-sts.us|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|accessdate=2012-06-06}}</ref>\n*Narda RadMan 2LT [https://www.narda-sts.com/en/personal-safety-emf/radman-2-xt-radman-2-lt-radman-radman-xt/eID/pd/p